title: Compressed Air Systems
description: OPC 11020: CESMII and OPC Foundation will develop a specification for an Internet-hosted database containing OPC UA information models. This database can be made publicly accessible through a RESTful interface. User access control will be handled through a separate identity provider. This cloud library can be made available to manufacturers who are looking to leverage industrial assets containing non-standardized information models for their SCADA or analytics systems.

  <UADataType NodeId="ns=1;i=3026" BrowseName="1:DryerOperatingStateEnum">
    <DisplayName>DryerOperatingStateEnum</DisplayName>
    <Documentation>https://reference.opcfoundation.org/v104/CAS/v100/docs/8.20</Documentation>
    <References>
      <Reference ReferenceType="HasSubtype" IsForward="false">i=29</Reference>
      <Reference ReferenceType="HasProperty">ns=1;i=10649</Reference>
    </References>
    <Definition Name="1:DryerOperatingStateEnum">
      <Field Name="Other" Value="0">
        <Description>The dryer is in a state not specified by this enumeration.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="Stopped" Value="1">
        <Description>The dryer is stopped. This state is applicable to all adsorption dryers.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="Running" Value="2">
        <Description>The dryer is running. This state is applicable to all dryers.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="RefrigerantCompressorStopped" Value="3">
        <Description>The compressor of the refrigerant circuit is standing still, and the refrigerant dryer is operating using the stored cold. This state is applicable to refrigerant dryers.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="RefrigerantCompressorRunning" Value="4">
        <Description>The compressor of the refrigerant circuit is running and compressing refrigerant, creating cold. This state is applicable to refrigerant dryers.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="PurgeValveClosed" Value="5">
        <Description>Purge valve is closed, and no purge air is consumed, no purge of the humidity from membranes dryer. This state is applicable to membrane dryers.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="PurgeValveOpen" Value="6">
        <Description>Purge air can flow to purge the humidity out of the membrane dryer. This state is applicable to membrane dryers.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="ParallelModeOfBothVessels" Value="7">
        <Description>Both vessels of the adsorption dryer are used in parallel for adsorption. This state is applicable to all adsorption dryers.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="Depressurizing" Value="8">
        <Description>One vessel of the adsorption dryer is depressurized for regeneration. This state is applicable to heatless and heated adsorption dryers, not HOC.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="Desorbing" Value="9">
        <Description>One vessel of the adsorption dryer is in desorption phase, using purge or ambient air, heated or not heated. This state is applicable to all adsorption dryers.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="Cooling" Value="10">
        <Description>One vessel of the adsorption dryer is being cooled after being heated in the previous desorption phase. This state is applicable to heated adsorption dryers and HOC.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="Pressurizing" Value="11">
        <Description>The depressurized vessel is pressurized again. This state is applicable to heatless and heated adsorption dryers, not HOC.</Description>
      </Field>
      <Field Name="RegeneratedVesselInStand-by" SymbolicName="RegeneratedVesselInStand_by" Value="12">
        <Description>The regenerated vessel is in standby and ready for adsorption phase. This state is applicable to all adsorption dryers.</Description>
      </Field>
    </Definition>
  </UADataType>

        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>3</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>RefrigerantCompressorStopped</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>The compressor of the refrigerant circuit is standing still, and the refrigerant dryer is operating using the stored cold. This state is applicable to refrigerant dryers.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>4</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>RefrigerantCompressorRunning</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>The compressor of the refrigerant circuit is running and compressing refrigerant, creating cold. This state is applicable to refrigerant dryers.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>5</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>PurgeValveClosed</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>Purge valve is closed, and no purge air is consumed, no purge of the humidity from membranes dryer. This state is applicable to membrane dryers.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>6</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>PurgeValveOpen</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>Purge air can flow to purge the humidity out of the membrane dryer. This state is applicable to membrane dryers.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>7</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>ParallelModeOfBothVessels</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>Both vessels of the adsorption dryer are used in parallel for adsorption. This state is applicable to all adsorption dryers.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>8</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>Depressurizing</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>One vessel of the adsorption dryer is depressurized for regeneration. This state is applicable to heatless and heated adsorption dryers, not HOC.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>9</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>Desorbing</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>One vessel of the adsorption dryer is in desorption phase, using purge or ambient air, heated or not heated. This state is applicable to all adsorption dryers.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>10</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>Cooling</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>One vessel of the adsorption dryer is being cooled after being heated in the previous desorption phase. This state is applicable to heated adsorption dryers and HOC.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>11</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>Pressurizing</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>The depressurized vessel is pressurized again. This state is applicable to heatless and heated adsorption dryers, not HOC.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
        <uax:ExtensionObject>
          <uax:TypeId>
            <uax:Identifier>i=7616</uax:Identifier>
          </uax:TypeId>
          <uax:Body>
            <uax:EnumValueType>
              <uax:Value>12</uax:Value>
              <uax:DisplayName>
                <uax:Text>RegeneratedVesselInStand-by</uax:Text>
              </uax:DisplayName>
              <uax:Description>
                <uax:Text>The regenerated vessel is in standby and ready for adsorption phase. This state is applicable to all adsorption dryers.</uax:Text>
              </uax:Description>
            </uax:EnumValueType>
          </uax:Body>
        </uax:ExtensionObject>
      </uax:ListOfExtensionObject>
    </Value>
  </UAVariable>
